==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Desistance
<hw>De*sist"ance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>desistance</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act or state of desisting;
cessation.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If fatigue of body or brain were in every case followed by
<qex>desistance</qex> . . . then would the system be but seldom out of
working order.</q> <rj><qau>H. Spencer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Desistive</ent>⟦br⟧
